{#
  localeChooserCustom — a thin wrapper around the canonical
  localeChooser macro that swaps the default globe glyph for a
  project-supplied inline SVG.

  This file is shipped with the examples directory so example 03
  (custom trigger) has something to import. In a real project, copy
  this wrapper into your own template directory so every locale
  switcher in the app shares one branded trigger.

  How the override works:

    The Nunjucks equivalent of "children" is a `{% call %}` block.
    Calling localeChooser with one replaces the default
    `<span class="locale-chooser-icon">` (which holds U+1F310 GLOBE
    WITH MERIDIANS) INSIDE the button with the block body. Everything
    else is untouched: the root <div>, the hidden input, the button's
    ARIA, and the <ul role="listbox"> of options all still come from
    the canonical macro, and the options still come from
    `opts.locales`.

    The call block does NOT render options. There is no way to
    replace the listbox from a call block — see below.

  Rules for the replacement glyph:

    - Mark it `aria-hidden="true"` (and `focusable="false"` on inline
      SVG). The button is icon-only; its accessible name is
      `opts.label` via `aria-label`, and visible glyph text would
      compete with it.
    - Keep it non-interactive. Nothing focusable belongs inside a
      <button>.
    - Prefer `currentColor` so consumer CSS drives the colour from
      `.locale-chooser-button`.

  When a call block is not enough:

    If you need a control the macro cannot render at all, skip the
    macro and hand-write the DOM with the same hooks —
    `data-lily-locale-chooser-root`, `-button`, `-list`, `-input`,
    plus `role="option"` and `data-value` on each choice.
    `initLocaleChooser(root)` works against any conforming DOM, and
    returns an inert controller when the button or the list is
    missing.

  Invoke this wrapper plainly — it takes no caller block of its own:

    {{ localeChooserCustom({label: "Language", locales: ["en", "fr"]}) }}
#}
{% from "../locale-chooser.njk" import localeChooser %}

{%- macro localeChooserCustom(opts) -%}
{% call localeChooser(opts) %}
    <svg
        class="locale-chooser-icon"
        viewBox="0 0 16 16"
        width="16"
        height="16"
        aria-hidden="true"
        focusable="false"
    >
        <circle cx="8" cy="8" r="7" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" />
        <ellipse cx="8" cy="8" rx="3" ry="7" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" />
        <line x1="1" y1="8" x2="15" y2="8" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" />
    </svg>
{% endcall %}
{%- endmacro -%}
